definition[0]: if birds or animals migrate, they travel regularly from one part of the world to another
definition[1]: if people migrate, they go to live in another area or country, especially in order to find work
definition[2]: to start using a different computer system, or to arrange for people to start using a different computer system
definition[3]: to move information or software from one computer system to another
definition[4]: to go to another area or country, especially in order to find work
example[0]: In the years ahead, tens of thousands of workers looking for high-paid, technical jobs could migrate abroad.
